# OrganizeEntropy

> A Win32 desktop utility for World of Warcraft players who have lost
> control of their account storage.

**Repository:** https://github.com/theskaf/OrganizeEntropy
**BagSync upstream:** https://github.com/Xruptor/BagSync
**Language:** Delphi 12 (Community Edition)
**Platform:** Windows (Win32)
**Database:** SQLite via FireDAC
**Last snapshot:** June 2026

---

## What Is This?

If you play World of Warcraft across multiple characters, a guild bank,
and a warband bank, you already know the problem: the same stackable
crafting reagent is sitting in five different bags across three
characters, your guild bank tab is a graveyard of half-stacks, and you
have no idea which character is holding that one item you actually need
right now.

OrganizeEntropy solves this by reading the
[BagSync](https://github.com/Xruptor/BagSync) addon's `SavedVariables`
file, loading every item on every character, guild bank tab, and warband
bank tab into a local SQLite database, and — once complete — suggesting
the optimal consolidation moves to free up as many bag slots as possible.

It is a **single-user, offline, read-only** tool. It never touches your
WoW installation or SavedVariables directly. It reads, analyses, and
advises. You do the moving in-game.

