## Prerequisites

### In-game (WoW side)
1. Install **[BagSync](https://github.com/Xruptor/BagSync)** — tracks
   item locations across all your characters automatically on login/logout.
2. Install the companion addon bundled in this repo:
   **OrganizeItemsThroughBagSyncExport** (folder in repo root).
   - Copy the folder to:
     `<WoW>\\_retail_\\Interface\\AddOns\\`
3. Log in to each character whose inventory you want tracked and let
   BagSync scan (open bags, bank, guild bank).
4. Run `/cie export` in-game, then `/reload` to flush the
   item metadata export to disk.
   > **Tip:** Run `/cie export` *after* opening your bags and bank,
   > not immediately on login — `C_Item.GetItemInfo` only returns data
   > for items the client has recently cached.

### On your PC (app side)
- Windows 10 or later (Win32)
- [Delphi 12 Community Edition](https://www.embarcadero.com/products/delphi)
  (to build from source)
- FireDAC SQLite driver (bundled with Delphi — no separate install)
- No internet connection required at runtime

