## Database Schema (Summary)

```sql
Owners        — one row per character / guild / warband
StorageTypes  — bag | bank | guildtab | warbandtab | reagentbank |
                auction | void | mail | equipped
Inventory     — one row per (owner, storage, container, item, quality variant)
Items         — item metadata from companion addon export
               (name, bind type, stack size, quality, etc.)
```

**Key design decisions:**
- `ItemString` (the raw item link before the `;count` separator) is
  included in the `Inventory` UNIQUE constraint so that crafting
  reagents with different quality tiers (e.g. Aqirite Q1 vs Q2) get
  distinct rows rather than being merged.
- `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE SET Count = Count + excluded.Count` handles
  the edge case where BagSync emits the same slot twice.
- `Items` is populated from the companion addon, not from BagSync.
  BagSync records item IDs and counts only — it does not export
  metadata.
- SQLite WAL mode is enabled for performance.
- Foreign keys are enforced (`ON DELETE RESTRICT`).

