## Known Limitations

| Limitation | Detail |
|------------|--------|
| One Battle.net account | BagSync only covers one account's WTF folder. Multiple accounts require symlink setup on the WoW side — see Future Ideas above. |
| Item cache dependency | `C_Item.GetItemInfo` in the companion addon returns `nil` for uncached items. Items not visited since login will be missing from the export. Re-run `/cie export` after opening bags/bank. |
| TOC version | `## Interface: 120001` in the companion addon `.toc` must be updated manually each major WoW patch, or the addon will show as "out of date". The game still loads it unless out-of-date addons are disabled. |
| No free slot data | BagSync records items that exist, not empty slots. Empty-slot move suggestions are not yet possible without additional data. |
| BoE/BoU equipped status | BagSync does not track whether a BoE/BoU item has already been equipped/used. The tool treats all BoE/BoU items as moveable. |
| No real-time sync | OrganizeEntropy reads a snapshot. Also: 
### BagSync Data Gaps
- **No empty slot tracking** — BagSync records items that *exist*; it does not record total bag/bank capacity or the number of empty slots per character. The consolidation engine's move suggestions will initially be limited to **co-location consolidation only** (merging stacks that already share a location). Full empty-slot move suggestions require one of: parsing bag size metadata from BagSync, user-entered slot capacities, or a future companion addon extension.
- **BoE/BoU equipped status unknown** — BagSync does not distinguish between an unequipped BoE item (still tradeable) and one that has been equipped (now soulbound). The consolidation engine will conservatively treat all BoE/BoU items as moveable and rely on the user to verify before acting.
- **Single Battle.net account only** — BagSync tracks one Battle.net account's WTF folder at a time. Users with multiple Battle.net accounts must set up WoW-side symlinks to merge SavedVariables folders. This is a BagSync architectural constraint, not an OrganizeEntropy one.
### Companion Addon (`OrganizeItemsThroughBagSyncExport`)
- **Client cache dependency** — `C_Item.GetItemInfo` returns `nil` for items not currently in the WoW client's cache. Items not visited (bags not opened, bank not visited) since the last login will be absent from the export. The recommended workflow is: log in → open all bags → visit bank → visit guild bank → run `/cie export` → `/reload`. Repeat across characters for full coverage.
- **TOC version must be manually updated** — The `## Interface:` line in `OrganizeItemsThroughBagSyncExport.toc` must be updated after each major WoW patch, or the addon will appear as "out of date" in the addon list. The game still loads it unless the player has explicitly disabled out-of-date addons. Automating this check is planned for Milestone E.
- **Items table coverage** — As of the June 2026 snapshot, approximately 6,999 inventory rows reference ItemIDs absent from the `Items` table. This is expected and will resolve progressively as the companion addon export is run across more characters and sessions.
### UI / Application
- **UI freezes during parse** — The current implementation reads and parses `BagSync.lua` synchronously on the main thread. For large accounts (files up to 10 MB, 50,000–100,000 rows), this causes a noticeable UI freeze. Async parsing via `TTask.Run` is planned for Milestone E.
- **No results display yet** — `StringGrid1` is declared in the DFM but not yet populated. The consolidation results UI is planned for Milestone C.
- **Guild filter checkboxes not wired** — `FlowPanelGuilds` is populated with one `TCheckBox` per guild found, but the checkboxes are not yet connected to any filtering logic. This is the core of Milestone B.
- **`LoadFromIni` not called on startup** — The INI-persisted BagSync path is written on manual file selection but not restored on `FormCreate` (auto-detection takes precedence). Full INI round-trip for both file paths is part of Milestone E.

