## Technical Reference

### Database Schema Summary

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Owners` | One row per character, guild, or warband. Keyed by `(OwnerType, OwnerName, Realm)`. |
| `StorageTypes` | Lookup table for normalized storage names (`bag`, `bank`, `guildtab`, `warbandtab`, etc.). |
| `Inventory` | One row per `(Owner, Storage, Container, ItemID, ItemString)`. `UNIQUE` constraint prevents duplicates; `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` sums counts. |
| `Items` | Item metadata from the companion addon. Populated separately from BagSync. `LEFT JOIN` — rows may be missing until the addon export covers the full item set. |

### Key Design Decisions

- **Way 3 (ItemString in UNIQUE key)** — Crafting reagents with quality tiers (e.g. Aqirite Q1 vs Q2) share the same base `ItemID` but differ in their `:bonus:` suffix. Including `ItemString` in the `UNIQUE` constraint guarantees a distinct row per quality variant, preventing incorrect stack merging.
- **Normalized lookup tables** — `Owners` and `StorageTypes` are separate tables rather than inline strings in `Inventory`, keeping rows compact and JOINs readable, particularly important given multi-byte UTF-8 characters (`©`, `§`) in owner names.
- **WAL journal mode** — SQLite is configured with `journal_mode=WAL` for improved read concurrency and parse performance. A full account import (50,000–100,000 rows) completes in under 2 seconds in a single transaction.
- **Container as TEXT** — Slot/tab identifiers are stored as `TEXT` rather than `INTEGER` to accommodate non-numeric container keys that appear in some BagSync storage types.

### Storage Type Reference

| BagSync Key | Normalized Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `bag` | `bag` | Character bags, slots 1–N |
| `bank` | `bank` | Character bank |
| `reagents` | `reagentbank` | Reagent bank tab |
| `void` | `void` | Void storage |
| `mail` | `mail` | Mailbox items |
| `auction` | `auction` | AH listings (extra `bag` nesting) |
| `equipped` | `equipped` | Currently worn items |
| `tabs` (Guild owner) | `guildtab` | Guild bank tab |
| `tabs` (Warband owner) | `warbandtab` | Warband bank tab |

### WoW Item Bind Types

| Value | Meaning | Moveable? |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | None (free trade) | ✅ Yes |
| 1 | Bind on Pickup (BoP) | ❌ No |
| 2 | Bind on Equip (BoE) | ✅ Yes (until equipped) |
| 3 | Bind on Use (BoU) | ✅ Yes (until used) |
| 4 | Quest item | ❌ No |

